ShopScout — Third-party Data Attribution
========================================

This extension bundles JSON files under `normalization/libraries/generated/`
that are derived from third-party open data sources. The generated files are
not the source data itself — they are compact indexed lookup tables extracted
by scripts under `scripts/build-normalization-libraries/`.

Attribution below is required by each source's license.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Schema.org
   -----------
   Files derived: `normalization/libraries/generated/schemaOrgProperties.json`
   Source vocabulary: https://schema.org/
   License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 (CC-BY-SA-3.0)
   Attribution: "This work incorporates canonical field names from
   Schema.org (https://schema.org/), used under CC-BY-SA-3.0."
   Notes: The generated JSON extracts a subset of Schema.org's
   Product + Offer + selected supertype properties to serve as canonical
   column names. Property URLs preserved in each entry.

2. Icecat Open Icecat
   ------------------
   Files derived: `normalization/libraries/generated/icecatVocabulary.json`,
                  `normalization/libraries/generated/icecatCategoryFeatures.json`
   Source vocabulary: https://icecat.biz/ (Open Icecat)
   License: Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0 (CC-BY-ND-4.0)
   Attribution: "This work incorporates enum vocabularies and category-feature
   mappings from Open Icecat (https://icecat.biz/), used under CC-BY-ND-4.0."
   Notes: The generated JSON extracts feature vocabularies and category-to-
   feature mappings. Icecat's data is included as reference lookup only —
   ShopScout does not modify Icecat's canonical values. Any user-editable
   normalization decisions layer on top via the extension's user rules
   overlay (`normalization/userRules.js`); Icecat's underlying data is
   preserved without modification.

3. Amazon Shopping Queries Dataset (ESCI)
   --------------------------------------
   Files derived: `normalization/libraries/generated/esciSubstitutes.json`
   Source vocabulary: https://github.com/amazon-science/esci-data
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Attribution: "This work incorporates substitute-product signal derived
   from the Amazon Shopping Queries Dataset (ESCI) by Amazon Science,
   used under Apache-2.0."
   Notes: The generated JSON extracts pairs of Amazon product identifiers
   (ASINs) labeled as substitutes for the same shopping query. ShopScout
   uses this as a bonus scoring signal in duplicate/substitute detection;
   it does not authoritatively determine product identity.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Non-inclusion policy
--------------------
The raw source files (Schema.org RDF/JSON-LD, Icecat XMLs, ESCI parquet
files) are NOT redistributed in this extension. They are consumed only at
build time under `data-sources/` (git-ignored) on the developer's local
machine. The generated JSON files under `normalization/libraries/generated/`
are the only artifacts shipped in the extension package.

Updating this NOTICE
--------------------
When adding a new generated library, update `SCHEMA.md` and this file
before the extension package is rebuilt. Removing or misrepresenting any
attribution above is a license violation for the affected source.
